      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 69.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 69.1 - 老子 69.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>用兵有言﹕「吾不敢為主而為客，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>A master of the art of war has said, 'I do not dare to be the host (to commence the war); I prefer to be the guest (to act on the defensive).</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-069__align-002">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-069</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 69.2 - 老子 69.3</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 69.3 - 老子 69.4</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>不敢進寸而退尺。」是謂行無行，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>I do not dare to advance an inch; I prefer to retire a foot.' This is called marshalling the ranks where there are no ranks;</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-069__align-003">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-069</prop>
